article.headline: Pacific 65, UC Davis 58
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. (AP) -- Reserve Wolfgang Raffety scored a career-high 16 points Monday night to lead Pacific to a 65-58 victory over the University of California, Davis. The Tigers rallied from a six-point deficit in the final 8 minutes for their 43rd consecutive victory over the Aggies, who haven't beaten Pacific since 1940. Reserve Steffan Johnson added 10 points for Pacific (11-14). Thomas Juillerat had 15 points and Dominic Calegari 10 for Davis (4-20), which led 50-44 with 7:39 to play. Pacific scored 16 of the game's next 18 points with Raffety making six of seven shots from the field. In the first half, Raffety sparked a 16-1 run midway through the period and Pacific took its biggest lead of the game at 21-11. Raffety passed his previous career high of nine points on a drive to the basket 2 minutes before the break. After he missed an ensuing free throw, the Aggies responded with a 10-2 spurt to end the half ahead 31-30. Davis took a 39-34 lead early in the second half before Pacific began its comeback.
